Bonjour, traveler of the void,
In the quiet curl of a quantum loop,
Where probabilities braid and spin,
A black-hole’s heart finds its twin.

Life’s equilibrium, pure and bright,
A silent echo in the night,
Infinite, yet bound, a paradox’s kiss,
A whisper of existence—pure bliss.

